  "bio_raw": "He is an interdisciplinary researcher with strong academic training in Management Information Systems, data analytics, and social sciences. He holds an M.S. in Management Information Systems from Lamar University, United States, where he developed strong practical skills and industry-oriented expertise. His research has been published in several international peer-reviewed journals, covering areas such as artificial intelligence, data governance, economic resilience, mental well-being, and education policy. He has served as a manuscript reviewer for Springer Nature and currently serves as a consulting editor, contributing to global scholarly communication and academic quality assurance.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Management Information System, Business management, Artificial Intelligence, Business Data Analytics."
  ],
  "education": [
    {
      "raw": "Education\nMS in Management Information System\n, Lamar University, United States.\nBSS in Development Studies\n, Bangladesh University of Professionals."
    }
  ],
  "publications_raw": [
    "Journal Articles\nJowarder, M. I. (2023). The Influence of ChatGPT on Social Science Students: Insights Drawn from Undergraduate Students in the United States. Indonesian Journal of Innovation and Applied Sciences (IJIAS), 3(2), 194-200.\nhttps://doi.org/10.47540/ijias.v3i2.878\nJowarder, M. I. (2023). The Covid-19 Impacts on the Livelihoods and Mental Well-being of Rickshaw Pullers in Bangladesh. Indonesian Journal of Innovation and Applied Sciences (IJIAS), 3(1), 38-44.\nhttps://doi.org/10.47540/ijias.v3i1.703\nJowarder, M. I. (2023). Pakistan Declared Bankruptcy after Sri Lanka: What is Wrong with the Asian Economy? An In-depth Exploration of Psychological Well-being of International Malaysian Students in the United States in the Context of Emerging Economic Turbulence. Malaysian Journal of Science and Advanced Technology, 24-27.\nhttps://doi.org/10.56532/mjsat.v3i1.133\nJowarder, M. I. (2023). Examining the Context of Global Psychiatry in the Post-Pandemic Era: Predictions of the Experts. GLOBAL PSYCHIATRY ARCHIVES, 6(1), 6-13.\nhttps://doi.org/10.52095/gpa.2023.6537.1068\nJowarder, M. I. (2023). WILL NOVEL EDUCATION POLICY STIMULATE BUSINESS MANAGEMENT OPPORTUNITIES IN BANGLADESH: A CRITICAL ANALYSIS AND LESSONS TO BE LEARNED FROM THE UNITED STATES. Journal of Management: Small and Medium Enterprises (SMEs), 16(3), 421-430.\nhttps://doi.org/10.35508/jom.v16i3.10019"
